title: Wales make three player changes for World Cup quarter-final against South Africa
text:
Wales make three player changes for World Cup quarter-final against South Africa 15 Oct 2015 10:17:16 
comments 
Wales head coach Warren Gatland has made three changes of personnel to his team for Saturday's Rugby World Cup quarter-final against South Africa at Twickenham. 
Newport Gwent Dragons centre Tyler Morgan starts in midfield alongside Jamie Roberts, while prop Gethin Jenkins returns instead of Paul James and flanker Dan Lydiate is in the back-row with skipper Sam Warburton and number eight Taulupe Faletau. 
Positional moves see George North revert to the wing after he started at centre against Australia in last weekend's Pool A decider, with Warburton switching from blindside to openside flanker. Related Sport News
